207
00:20:25,816 --> 00:20:31,980
[SPEAKER_11]: So probably the biggest thing here to talk about would be the temporary sprinkler system during construction.

208
00:20:32,780 --> 00:20:41,745
[SPEAKER_11]: You did see here, I referenced a couple of things, one of them being the significant fire risk that this type of design will impose.

209
00:20:42,305 --> 00:20:44,766
[SPEAKER_11]: So I have firsthand experience with this.

210
00:20:46,626 --> 00:20:55,153
[SPEAKER_11]: A project of very similar magnitude was being constructed in Waltham, and we had one of the largest construction fires in the United States in 2017.

211
00:20:55,553 --> 00:21:07,223
[SPEAKER_11]: I was the building commissioner at the time, and the conflagration of the fire was so extreme that not only was it a total loss, but the building basically disintegrated while it was under construction.

212
00:21:08,284 --> 00:21:11,126
[SPEAKER_11]: The City Council and the Zoning Board of Appeals then

213
00:21:12,197 --> 00:21:19,540
[SPEAKER_11]: looked into what actions they could actually take as part of, you know, trying to make these things safer while under construction.

214
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:29,724
[SPEAKER_11]: The best thing that they came up with at the time was a temporary construction sprinkler system in which a dry action system is basically built as the building is being constructed.

215
00:21:30,324 --> 00:21:32,085
[SPEAKER_11]: It's not extremely technical.

216
00:21:32,165 --> 00:21:40,408
[SPEAKER_11]: It does require a couple of extra steps, but I have, basically, I have pulled all three of the

217
00:21:42,220 --> 00:21:44,722
[SPEAKER_11]: projects that we require temporary sprinkles on.

218
00:21:44,742 --> 00:21:55,810
[SPEAKER_11]: A couple of them actually volunteered because it was such a significant fire risk that they were actually able to keep their insurance rates down a little bit by having this system somewhat active during construction.

219
00:21:55,850 --> 00:22:02,675
[SPEAKER_11]: And basically what it is, it's a pre-action system that is basically livened up with air in the lines at nighttime.

220
00:22:03,212 --> 00:22:12,895
[SPEAKER_11]: It is set off by a, just very simply put, it has to be set off by both a fire popping a sprinkler head and a heat detection system also going off.

221
00:22:12,935 --> 00:22:18,096
[SPEAKER_11]: And then it has to be manually triggered by somebody remotely on site to get water into the system.

222
00:22:18,516 --> 00:22:20,537
[SPEAKER_11]: Now, ideally, it's not rated.

223
00:22:20,597 --> 00:22:29,459
[SPEAKER_11]: It's not a system that is basically outlined in reference standards.

224
00:22:29,479 --> 00:22:32,640
[SPEAKER_11]: So in other words, they don't have a reference standard for a temporary sprinkler system.

225
00:22:33,233 --> 00:22:40,699
[SPEAKER_11]: However, it does afford some protection during construction that otherwise would not be afforded if the building was completely dry.

226
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:53,990
[SPEAKER_11]: Cooper Street, and the only reason I say this is because Cooper Street was a pretty, you know, a pretty massive fire.

227
00:22:54,130 --> 00:22:56,091
[SPEAKER_11]: It just, it's an exception to the rule.

228
00:22:56,131 --> 00:23:01,756
[SPEAKER_11]: It's not something that you would see happen, but actually they determined that it was a suspicious fire and it was started by an arsonist.

229
00:23:02,965 --> 00:23:17,911
[SPEAKER_11]: And so that triggered off the need for not only for these temporary sprinkler systems to be built on wood frame construction only, but also a pretty sophisticated security system that would allow for deterrence at night.

230
00:23:18,051 --> 00:23:28,855
[SPEAKER_11]: And so these things have been written into not only 40B comprehensive permits, but also into special permits for FAR in the city that I formerly worked in.

231
00:23:29,490 --> 00:23:35,273
[SPEAKER_11]: and this basically would afford some additional fire safety during construction.

232
00:23:35,314 --> 00:23:45,540
[SPEAKER_11]: My concern about this, okay, my concern about this design, okay, it maximizes the amount of wood frame construction that's allowed under the IBC.

233
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:54,665
[SPEAKER_11]: This particular design I actually denied when I was the building commissioner in Waltham and I was overturned by the building code appeals board.

